</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="278" pageNumber="883" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="278.[1396,2603,726,1312]" pageId="278" pageNumber="883">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1399,1747,1081,1115]" pageId="278" pageNumber="883">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Critically Endangered on The IUCN Red List but could be soon declared extinct. The Ethiopian Amphibious Rat is known from a single individual collected in 1927; despite many searches, it has not been found again. Its original habitat has been destroyed and is now overgrazed by cattle.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
